Warren W. Woodcock (22 September 1936 â€“ 5 February 2022) was an Australian amateur tennis player who competed in the 1950s and 1960s. He reached the quarterfinals of the Australian Championships in 1957 and the final of a US Pro Championship in 1967, losing to Sam Giammalva.
After retiring from tennis he became an on-course bookmaker.
